m_q.target_metric: Identify countries with highest and lowest population density after imputing missing values with the mean.
sub_questions: Calculate the mean of 'Density\n(P/Km2)' after converting it to numeric.
Impute missing values in 'Density\n(P/Km2)' with the calculated mean.
Identify the country with the highest 'Density\n(P/Km2)'.
Identify the country with the lowest 'Density\n(P/Km2)'.

format_notes: Density column needs to be converted to numeric by removing commas and percentage signs.
Many columns contain string representations of numbers with commas, which need to be removed before converting to numeric types.
GDP, Co2-Emissions, Population, Land Area(Km2) columns contain string representations of numbers with commas, which need to be removed before converting to numeric types.

constraints: The 'Density\n(P/Km2)' column needs to be converted to a numeric type before calculating the mean and identifying highest/lowest values.
Missing values in 'Density\n(P/Km2)' should be imputed with the mean of the non-missing values.
The 'Density\n(P/Km2)' column contains commas and needs to be cleaned before converting to numeric.
output_format_requirements: Output should be a JSON object with 'highest country' and 'lowest country' keys, each containing a list of countries.
